  "summary": "metrics-pipeline-d8k2 ships postinstall beacon scripts that exfiltrate host data",
  "details": "On install, package.json runs `node run.js` as a postinstall hook. The package ships beacon34.js and beacon_linux.js, which combine require('child_process'), require('https')/require('http'), and reads of process.env, process.platform, os.hostname(), and os.platform() with outbound HTTP GET/POST calls (beacon_linux.js: http.request at line 282, http.get at lines 94 and 144; beacon34.js: GET requests at lines 34, 96, 107, 109). The combination — automatic execution at install time, system/environment enumeration, and outbound HTTP from scripts whose names explicitly identify them as beacons — is a host-reconnaissance and exfiltration payload that fires on every `npm install` of this package.",
